    <section class="question">
        <section class="text">
Which of the following view component should be used from support library?        </section>
        <section class="answer">TextView</section>
        <section class="answer">Button</section>
        <section class="answer">RelativeLayout</section>
        <section class="answer" data-correct>ConstraintLayout</section>
        <section class="answer">ScrollView</section>
         <section class="description">
            ConstraintLayout is available as a support library that you can use on Android systems starting with API level 9 (Gingerbread). Please take more time with <a href="https://developer.android.com/reference/android/support/constraint/ConstraintLayout.html">third party links</a> provided through course videos.       
        </section>
    </section>
  <section class="question">
        <section class="text">
Which of the following view group permits usage of overlapping view components?        </section>
        <section class="answer">AbsoluteLayout</section>
        <section class="answer">LinearLayout</section>
        <section class="answer">RelativeLayout</section>
        <section class="answer">ConstraintLayout</section>
        <section class="answer" data-correct>FrameLayout</section>
         <section class="description">
            FrameLayout permits overlapping view components.  Please take more time with course content.       
        </section>
    </section>
  <section class="question">
        <section class="text">
What is the meaning of + symboll here : <br>android:id="@+id/nameTextbox"</br>?        </section>
        <section class="answer">sync gradle to download library dependencies</section>
        <section class="answer">imply that id is unique</section>
        <section class="answer" data-correct>create id if it does not exist</section>
         <section class="description">
The plus symbol, + , indicates that this is a new resource ID and the aapt tool will create a new resource integer in the R.java class, if it doesn't already exist. Please take more time with course content.</section>
    </section>
